RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 84. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDER OF ZION tracked the moderate early pace, waited for racing room while along the rail nearing the quarter marker, advanced in upper stretch, assumed command inside of the furlong marker and kept to task in the final stages. UNION GIG forwardly placed in the early going, pressed the moderate pace to the quarter marker, swung three wide for the drive, could not match strides with THUNDER OF ZION in the final furlong and held safely in the end for place. NEXT JOURNEY allowed to settle in the early stages, raced along the rail to the quarter marker, angled out inside of the furlong pole, closed well in deep stretch and was up for show in the final strides. GATOR SHINING broke alertly then took back to the track the pace, raced outside of rivals on the turn, swung four wide for the drive, ran evenly to mid-stretch, was outkicked in the final sixteenth and was just edged for show in the final strides. JUST WATCH ME NOW showed early speed and dictated terms to the turn, set a pressured pace to the quarter marker, could not keep pace with the winner in mid-stretch and gave way late. BIG STORY chased the moderate pace, raced three wide on the turn and did not threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Next Journey
ENTRY.OWNER: A Jason Hall Stables Shake and Bake Racing LLC and Baker Stephen R

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5F All Weather Track CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COUSIN RICHIE lacked early speed, trailed along the turn, circled the field to go five wide into the drive, closed with a rush inside of the furlong pole while on the left lead and overtook LOOKSGOODONYOUTHO in deep stretch to prevail. LOOKSGOODONYOUTHO hustled to establish the early lead, set moderate fractions to the quarter marker, drew clear nearing the furlong marker, felt pressure from COUSIN RICHIE inside of the sixteenth-marker, could not hold off that quickly oncoming rival and held for place. ALTITUDE chased the early pace, raced between rivals while in pursuit on the turn, was outrun in upper stretch, re-rallied in the late stages but was outfinished while well clear in the end for third. WOLF'S LIFE forwardly placed in the early stages, stalked the moderate pace inside of LOOKSGOODONYOUTHO entering the turn, lost ground in upper stretch and finished evenly in the final furlong. HOT ROD JIMMY close up in the early stages, raced four then three wide on the turn, was outrun in upper stretch and did not offer a late rally. PASSION OF JOE'S rated off of the moderate early pace, saved ground to the top of the lane and did not factor in the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Passion of Joe's
ENTRY.OWNER: Domeyko Taylor LP Moger Inc S Tsujimoto LLC Kropp Gary Kropp Janet and Pimentel

ENTRY.NAME: Altitude
ENTRY.OWNER: A Jason Hall Stables and Baker Stephen R

ENTRY.NAME: Hot Rod Jimmy
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up,4-3wide turn,outrun upper,no late rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 5F All Weather Track CR: 85. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming And Starter Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXCESSIVE CAT broke alertly then took back to press the solid early pace, kept close attendance to DARKSABER while outside of that rival to the quarter marker, battled to mid-stretch, overtook DARKSABER inside of the sixteenth-marker and determinedly kept to task to prevail. UNCLE WILBUR chased the solid early pace, advanced three wide on the turn, ran evenly to the furlong grounds, closed fast in deep stretch and just missed for the win, while getting up in time to secure place. DARKSABER sent to dispute the early pace, assumed command and set solid fractions while pressured to the quarter marker, held EXCESSIVE CAT at bay to mid-stretch, stubbornly yielded in deep stretch and was just edged for place. MINOSO crowded a bit at the start but recovered to be close to the early pace, saved ground while stalking the pace to the quarter pole, ran evenly while within aim to the furlong marker and was outkicked in the final stages. THIRSTY ALWAYS chased the solid early fractions, raced four wide to the quarter marker, was outrun in upper stretch and did not factor in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Darksaber
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,set pressured pace,held foes at bay 1/16,stubbornly gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Thirsty Always
ENTRY.OWNER: Roper James L and Roper Ilene A

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1M All Weather Track CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARSON'S LEGACY tracked the early pace, well placed through moderate fractions to the half-mile marker, roused four wide nearing the top of the lane, drew to even terms in mid-stretch and kicked clear in the final sixteenth. SHANAGOLDEN hopped at the start and was off slowly, allowed to settle, mounted a five wide rally leaving the far turn, closed with good interest in the drive, could not impact the winner in deep stretch but finished well in the end to secure the place. TIGER'S ARROW forwardly placed in the early stages, stalked the moderate pace to the second turn, made a steady advance nearing the quarter marker, continued that bid to mid-stretch, vied for the lead at the furlong marker, was outkicked in the final stages and held safely for show. AFRICAN PRINCE unhurried early on, trailed to the quarter marker, was unable to impact the top three in deep stretch but was gaining in the final sixteenth. MANY AMBITIONS broke alertly and showed good early speed, set a pressured pace along the first turn then disputed the moderate pace with KING ROB through the second turn, shook free of that rival in upper stretch, battled to the furlong marker and faded in the late going. VIVA LEON JODIDO crowded at the start by KING ROB and was away slowly, was a bit rank in the early stages, saved ground to the second turn and did not produce a rally in the stretch run. PICK BYMY FRIEND settled off of the early pace while not far back, advanced nearing the quarter marker, continued that bid in upper stretch, came within aim in mid-stretch, took up while in tight quarters nearing the sixteenth-marker and gave way in the final stages. KING ROB crowded VIVA LEON JODIDO at the start, showed early speed and contested the moderate pace, disputed the fractions with MANY AMBITIONS to the quarter marker, lost ground nearing mid-stretch and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Viva Leon Jodido
ENTRY.OWNER: Palacios Diane and Rich Eddie L
ENTRY.COMMENT: bothered start,bit rank early,saved ground,no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Many Ambitions
ENTRY.COMMENT: good early speed,disputed pace,battled to 1/8,faded late

ENTRY.NAME: Pick Bymy Friend
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled,not far back,bid,aim 1/8,took up 1/16,gave way late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 90. Claiming Purse 21000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRYSTAL PROOF broke in good order and set the pace to the turn, well handled while carving moderate fractions to the quarter marker, maintained a clear lead to mid-stretch, felt late pressure from the runner-up and held in a drive at the end to prevail. CIELO DIAMANTE took back off of the early pace, advanced on the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, finished well in the final furlong, put mild pressure on the winner in deep stretch but could not reel in CRYSTAL PROOF and was second best. MAGICAL LADY away a bit slowly, allowed to settle in the early stages, advanced on the turn, rallied inside of rivals in upper stretch, raced on the left lead in deep stretch, could not impact the top pair in the final stages but was clear for show in the end. CITY GLITTER forwardly placed in the early stages, tracked the moderate pace while two deep to the quarter marker, was outrun in upper stretch and lacked a late rally. TAMARA MINE settled in the second flight in the early stages, chased three wide on the turn and offered mild late rally. I'LL DO IT FOR YOU stalked the early pace while outside of rivals, chased CRYSTAL PROOF to the quarter marker, was outrun nearing the top of the lane and gave way. SMILIN EVIE chased from the rear early on, dropped back on the turn and was not a factor in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Magical Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: off bit slow,settled,inside rally,left lead,clear for 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Cielo Diamante
ENTRY.COMMENT: took back,gain turn,evenly to 1/8,finished well,2nd best

ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne

ENTRY.NAME: City Glitter
ENTRY.OWNER: Martin, Jerry R. and Margaret M.
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace,2wide turn,outrun upper,no late rally

ENTRY.NAME: I'll Do It for You
ENTRY.OWNER: Miller Quentin B Orsi Bernardo and Schmitt George F

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 6F All Weather Track CR: 69. Waiver Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIZZY DAZMURA crowded a bit soon after the start, chased from the second flight while along the rail, navigated traffic along the turn, found a seam in upper stretch, came within aim nearing the furlong marker, took a narrow lead inside of the sixteenth-marker and determinedly prevailed in the final strides. GRANOLA GIRL bobbled at the start then was shuffled back in the early stages and was unhurried into the turn, trailed to the quarter marker, swung five wide for the drive, advanced in mid-stretch, closed fast in deep stretch and just missed for the win, while getting up in the final strides for place. RHONDA'S COOKIN chased the early pace from the second flight, advanced on the turn while between runners, swung three wide for the drive, battled with HANNAH IN A HURRY to mid-stretch, drifted out in deep stretch, recovered in the late stages but was outfinished in the final strides, while just missing for second. HANNAH IN A HURRY raced close up to the early pace, pressed the pace three wide to the quarter marker, battled with RHONDA'S COOKIN to mid-stretch, was outkicked in the late stages and just missed for third. NATALIA chased the moderate early pace, raced four wide on the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, came in tight in deep stretch, steadied nearing the sixteenth-marker when RHONDA'S COOKIN drifted out and finished evenly in the late stages. HEAVEN'S GHOST forwardly placed in the early stages, pressed the pace to the quarter marker, was outrun in upper stretch and weakened. FLAPS UP broke alertly, set the early pressured pace, dueled with HEAVEN'S GHOST to the quarter marker, dropped back leaving the turn and tired in the drive. THERE WAS A JOCKEY'S OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF NATALIA AGAINST THE RIDER OF RHONDA'S COOKIN FOR THE INCIDENT IN DEEP STRETCH AND IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH BASED ON THE INCIDENT.

ENTRY.NAME: Flaps Up
ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,set pressured pace,dropped back,tired stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Granola Girl
ENTRY.OWNER: The Warnick Stable and Hinkhouse Joseph A

ENTRY.NAME: Hannah in a Hurry
ENTRY.OWNER: Orsi Bernardo and Schmitt George F

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 6F All Weather Track CR: 99. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 32000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $62,500. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since October 15 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAGER took back off of the fast early pace, saved ground to the quarter marker, roused in upper stretch, drew to even terms with IRREFUTABLE inside of the furlong pole, battled with that game rival to deep stretch and determinedly held on for the win over the oncoming runner-up. ULTIMATE BANGO bumped with HIGHLAND GHOST at the start and was off a step slowly, chased from the rear in the early stages, advanced on the turn, swung four then five wide for the drive, loomed nearing the furlong pole, chased the top pair to deep stretch, was outfinished in the final strides by RAGER and was up in time to secure the place. IRREFUTABLE broke alertly and showed speed to dictate terms early on, crowded WAR GAMES a bit nearing the half-mile marker then was pressed by that rival to the quarter pole, was confronted in mid-stretch, battled gamely to deep stretch and was outfinished in the final strides, while clear of the rest for third. HIGHLAND GHOST bumped with ULTIMATE BANGO at the start, recovered and tracked the fast pace to the turn, advanced three wide nearing the quarter marker, swung four wide for the drive, chased to mid-stretch and flattened out in the final furlong. WAR GAMES prominent in the early stages, pressed IRREFUTABLE while inside of that rival then came in tight nearing the half-mile marker and took to pressing outside of the pacesetter to the turn, kept close attendance to the quarter marker, dropped back in upper stretch and weakened in the late stages.

ENTRY.NAME: War Games
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace,in tight 1/2,dropped back upper,weakened stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 89. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since October 15 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A DIME FOR ME broke alertly, allowed the pace scenario to play out from a few lengths back, eased towards the leaders with three furlongs to go while staying in the three or four path, was set down in earnest at the top of the stretch and ran on well despite being on the wrong lead to win going away. DON'T TELL HYDEE broke well and went immediately for the early lead, seemed comfortable with the pace through the turn, finished strongly and was no match for the winner but held the place. GET'EM TIGER broke out a bit but quickly straightened out, tracked the pacesetter to the turn, moved up to challenge for the lead passing the quarter pole, was in the middle of the leading trio turning for home, was outkicked in the final furlong and held well for show in the late stages. MAYCEE JO tracked the pace while saving ground, tipped out a path for the stretch run and was gradually gaining ground but needed a bit more. ROSE PRINCESS broke a little awkwardly and spotted the field a head start, went wide around the turn and entered the stretch in the four path, never able to make an impact. DANCING CRANE close early, had trouble keeping up from the five-sixteenths, came under heavy pressure passing the quarter pole but had nothing to offer in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Maycee Jo
ENTRY.OWNER: Earley Brian Fasi Gina McLean Bill and Planchon Doug

ENTRY.COMMENT: set comfortable pace, responded to challenge, held place

ENTRY.COMMENT: spotted field head start, wide turn, never made an impact

ENTRY.OWNER: Landeros David and Landeros Jorge T
